---
title: Motion GPU Documentation
description: Framework-agnostic WebGPU core with Svelte 5, React 18/19, and Vue 3 adapters for fullscreen WGSL rendering.
---

`@motion-core/motion-gpu` ships a **framework-agnostic WebGPU core** plus **Svelte 5**, **React 18/19**, and **Vue 3** adapters for fullscreen WGSL rendering. You get a declarative material system, a reactive frame scheduler, a composable post-processing pipeline, and **GPU compute shader support** — wired into a single `<FragCanvas>` component in all three adapters.

This documentation was generated directly from the `packages/motion-gpu/src` source tree, so every contract, default value, and edge-case behavior described here reflects the actual implementation.

## AI documentation access

Motion GPU documentation is also available for AI tools via [Context7](https://context7.com/motion-core/motion-gpu).

## What this package ships

| Area | Source of truth | What it does |
| --- | --- | --- |
| **Svelte runtime component** | `svelte/FragCanvas.svelte` | Owns the `<canvas>`, provides Svelte context/hooks, and bridges props/runtime state into the core loop. |
| **React runtime component** | `react/FragCanvas.tsx` | Owns the `<canvas>`, provides React context/hooks, and bridges props/runtime state into the core loop. |
| **Vue runtime component** | `vue/FragCanvas.vue` | Owns the `<canvas>`, provides Vue provide/inject composables, and bridges props/runtime state into the core loop. |
| **Runtime loop (core)** | `core/runtime-loop.ts` | Runs requestAnimationFrame, renderer rebuild policy, frame scheduling, render gating, and normalized error routing. |
| **Material pipeline** | `material.ts` + `material-preprocess.ts` | Validates fragment shaders, expands `#include` / `defines`, and produces deterministic pipeline signatures. |
| **Renderer** | `renderer.ts` | Handles WebGPU device init, shader compilation, uniform buffer writes, texture uploads, and render-graph execution. |
| **Frame scheduler** | `core/frame-registry.ts` + `svelte/frame-context.ts` + `react/frame-context.ts` + `vue/frame-context.ts` | Orchestrates ordered frame tasks, stage graphs, invalidation tokens, render-mode gating, and optional profiling (core), with Svelte/React/Vue hook-context adapter wrappers. |
| **Pass system** | `render-graph.ts` + `passes/*` | Implements an extensible pass graph with ping-pong slots (`source`/`target`), named render targets, optional canvas output, three built-in render pass types, and two compute pass types (`ComputePass`, `PingPongComputePass`). |
| **Compute pipeline** | `compute-shader.ts` + `storage-buffers.ts` | Builds compute shader WGSL, validates contracts, manages storage buffer allocation/readback, and dispatches compute workgroups within the render graph. |
| **Texture loading** | `core/texture-loader.ts` + `svelte/use-texture.ts` + `react/use-texture.ts` + `vue/use-texture.ts` | Fetches, decodes, and caches texture URLs with abort/reload race safety and reactive adapter state. |
| **Diagnostics** | `error-report.ts` + `error-diagnostics.ts` | Maps low-level WebGPU and WGSL errors to structured reports with hints and source snippets. |

